#random forest classifier and feature importance

def randomforest_visualization(X, y, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, title):
    from sklearn.datasets import make_classification
    feature_names = [X.columns]
    forest = RandomForestClassifier(oob_score = True, random_state=0)
    forest.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    
    y_pred_rf = forest.predict(X_test)
    acc_score = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_rf)
    
    importances = forest.feature_importances_
    std = np.std([tree.feature_importances_ for tree in forest.estimators_], axis=0)

    forest_importances = pd.Series(importances, index=feature_names)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    forest_importances.plot.bar(yerr=std, ax=ax)
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.set_ylabel("Mean decrease in impurity")
    fig.autofmt_xdate(rotation=45)
    fig.tight_layout()
    
    print(f'Accuracy score: {acc_score}')
    print(f'Oob score: {forest.oob_score_}')
